---
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>MORN - Xi Lin</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-gray-900">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-16 sm:px-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900">Back to home</a>
      <p class="mt-6 text-sm font-mono text-blue-600">IROS 2026 | Under Review | First Author</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">MORN: Metacognitive Object-Goal Regulation for Resource-Rational Long-Horizon Navigation</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-4xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
        MORN adds a metacognitive executive layer to frozen VLM-based navigation backbones for long-horizon multi-goal navigation. The core idea is to regulate persistence, switching, and evidence accumulation under strict resource constraints so that the agent avoids wasting most of its budget on infeasible goals.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/papers/MORN.pdf" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-gray-900 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-gray-700">Download PDF</a>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 overflow-hidden rounded-[28px] border border-gray-200 bg-white">
        <img src="/assets/projects/morn-arch.png" alt="MORN architecture" class="w-full object-contain" />
      </div>

      <section class="mt-10 rounded-[28px] border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6 sm:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Abstract Summary</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
          MORN is motivated by the observation that standard zero-shot ObjectNav systems behave as purely reactive agents and often fall into a sunk-cost trap in long multi-goal missions. The framework introduces a System-2-style meta-controller that monitors progress velocity, perceptual uncertainty, and temporal stability, enabling the agent to abort zombie goals early and preserve budget for solvable targets.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="rounded-[28px] border border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
          <video controls playsinline class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-black">
            <source src="/assets/projects/morn-sim-demo.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          </video>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold">Simulation Demo</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            Simulation results show how MORN regulates multi-goal scheduling under constrained resources and reduces wasted-step behavior compared with reactive baselines.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="rounded-[28px] border border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
          <video controls playsinline class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-black">
            <source src="/assets/projects/morn-real-demo.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          </video>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold">Real-Robot Demo</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            The real-robot demo highlights how the executive layer remains useful beyond simulation by improving long-horizon target scheduling and execution behavior.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
